
Node.js Project with MySQL Sequelize
Welcome to this Node.js project using MySQL Sequelize! This README file will guide you through the steps to set up and run your project locally.

Prerequisites
Make sure you have the following installed on your machine:

Node.js
npm
MySQL installed and running

Getting Started
Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/talibackend/tidmuv-backend.git

Change into the project directory:
cd your-project

Install project dependencies:

npm install

Create a MySQL database for your project.

Update the database configuration:

Open the .env file and update the development section with your MySQL database credentials.

APP_KEY=
NODE_ENV=
PORT=
DB_HOST=
DB_USER=
DB_PASS=
DB_DATABASE=
DB_PORT=3306

Development
To start the development server and run your project:

npm run dev

This command will start the server using ts-node, which will automatically restart the server when changes are detected.

Visit http://localhost:${YOUR SET PORT} in your browser to see your Node.js application in action.

Project Structure
app/: Contains your application logic.
config/: Configuration files, including database configuration.
models/: Sequelize model definitions.
controllers/:Control what comes from the services.
routes/: API routes.
services/: Business logics of the project.
utils/: Reuseable functions.
middleware/: Authorization and Authentication.


Additional Notes
Make sure to keep sensitive information, such as database credentials, secure. Consider using environment variables for configuration.
Update the .gitignore file to exclude sensitive files or directories.
Ensure your MySQL server is running before starting the application.